types.section:
{{fr-adv}}

# [[so]], [[such]] {{gloss|intensifier}}
#: {{ux|fr|J’étais '''si''' fatigué ces jours-ci que je n’avais pas le courage de vous écrire.|t=I was '''so''' tired those days that I didn't have the energy to write to you.}}
#: {{ux|fr|Cela n'aurait pas été une '''si''' bonne idée.|t=That wouldn't have been '''such''' a good idea.}}
# {{q|si + adjective/adverb + que ... }} [[however]] {{gloss|to whatever extent or degree}}
#: {{syn|fr|aussi|tout|quelque}}
#: {{ux|fr|'''Si''' bavard qu'il soit, il ne dit rien de stupide.|t='''However''' talkative he may be, he doesn't say anything stupid.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=2017|author=Luc Brisson|title=Platon
|passage=Mais un législateur qui aurait un tant soit peu de worth, '''si''' infime soit elle, quand bien même il n'en irait pas comme l'argument vient de le démontrer, n'aurait-il pas commis en cette occasion, plus qu'en n'importe quelle autre circonstance où il aurait eu l'audace de mentir aux jeunes gens dans l'intérêt du bien, son plus utile mensonge, celui capable de faire que tous, non pas de force mais de leur plein gré, se conduisent de façon entièrement juste ?
|translation=But a legislator who would have the slightest bit of valour, '''however''' tiny it may be, even if it were not as the argument has just demonstrated, would he not have committed on this occasion, more than in any other circumstance where he would have had the audacity to lie to young people in the interest of the good, his most useful lie, the one capable of making everyone, not by force but of their own accord, behave in an entirely just fashion?}}

=====Usage notes=====
* In the sense {{m|en|however}}, the verb is usually in the subjunctive.
* The {{m|fr|que}} is sometimes replaced by an inverted-subject construction with a subjunctive verbal element and nominal, usually a personal pronoun.
*: {{ux|inline=1|fr|si heureuse soit-elle|however happy she may be}}
*: {{ux|inline=1|fr|si faible paraisse-t-il|however weak he may seem}}

{{head|fr|conjunctions}}

# [[if]], [[whether]]
#: {{uxi|fr|Je me demande '''si''' elle sera seule.|t=I wonder '''if''' she'll be alone.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Je veux savoir '''si''' tu viendras ou non.|t=I want to know '''if''' you're coming or not.}}
# [[if]] {{gloss|assuming that}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Si''' j'avais ses pouvoirs, je créerais un monde où le mal n'existe pas.|'''If''' I had his power, I'd create a world where evil didn't exist.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Si''' tu n'avais pas appelé, je serais morte.|'''If''' you hadn't called, I'd be dead.}}
# [[even if]]
# [[although]], [[while]]

=====Usage notes=====
Elided preceding {{m|fr|il}} or {{m|fr|ils}}, resulting in the contracted forms {{m|fr|s'il}} and {{m|fr|s'ils}}.

